Package: gghourglass
Title: Plot Records per Time of Day
Version: 0.0.0.9001
Authors@R: c(person("Pepijn", "de Vries", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "pepijn.devries@outlook.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7961-6646")),
    person("Lagerveld", "Sander", role = c("dtc"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1291-4021")))
Author:
    Pepijn de Vries [aut, cre] (0000-0002-7961-6646),
    Sander Lagerveld [dtc] (0000-0003-1291-4021)
Description: Splits date and time of day from continuous
    datetime objects and plots them using grammar of graphics
    ('ggplot2'). Plots can also be decorated with solar cycle
    information (e.g., sunset, sunrise, etc.). This is useful
    for data that are driven by time of day.
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
